commit.message: Removed unnecessary variable to satisfy linter.
For some reason (may be because we now always run tests in a subprocess), test_concurrent_fixture started to fail. Running pytest in a subprocess fixes some issues with capturing test stdout.
No need in SafeNumber, because processes report back to the main process and it keeps all stats.
Fixed hanging when tests-per-worker is large than 1.
Making flake8 happy.
Fixed hanging when pytest is running with --workers=1.

JUnit xml report generation was fixed.

Previosly, pytest_runtest_logreport hook was called inside forked
processed, and main pytest process wasn't able to know about test
results.

This fix uses a separate multiprocessing Queue to pass results back
to the main process.

[WIP] ci: report coverage via codecov (#57)

* ci: report coverage via codecov

Fixes https://github.com/browsertron/pytest-parallel/issues/56.

* rebuild
ci: Travis: separate lint job (#55)

Implement pytest's default pytest_runtestloop (#52)

* Fix return code when there is a collection error

* Implement/copy first part of pytest's pytest_runtestloop

Ref: https://github.com/browsertron/pytest-parallel/pull/45#issuecomment-557346297

Add test_collection_collectonly

commit.message:
ci: minor improvements (#48)

* ci: use PYTEST_ADDOPTS=-vv

* ci: Travis: remove unneeded "sudo: required"

Reraise (internal) exceptions (#49)

* Call queue.task_done always

This is needed with exceptions inside of `run_test` to not make
pytest-parallel hang then.

Fixes hanging `tests/test_general.py::test_environ_shim[cli_args1]`
test.

* Collect and reraise (internal) errors

Uses https://github.com/ionelmc/python-tblib for pickling the
tracebacks.

* squash! Collect and reraise (internal) errors

Include thread name.

Bump urllib3 from 1.23 to 1.24.2 (#43)

Bumps [urllib3](https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3) from 1.23 to 1.24.2.
- [Release notes](https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/releases)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/blob/master/CHANGES.rst)
- [Commits](https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/compare/1.23...1.24.2)

Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>

SafeNumber: add __ge__, __le__, __repr__ (#51)

Fixes https://github.com/browsertron/pytest-parallel/issues/37.

Call queue.task_done always (#47)

This is needed with exceptions inside of `run_test` to not make
pytest-parallel hang then.

Fixes hanging `tests/test_general.py::test_environ_shim[cli_args1]`
test.

Bump requests from 2.19.1 to 2.20.0 (#53)

Bumps [requests](https://github.com/requests/requests) from 2.19.1 to 2.20.0.
- [Release notes](https://github.com/requests/requests/releases)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/psf/requests/blob/master/HISTORY.md)
- [Commits](https://github.com/requests/requests/compare/v2.19.1...v2.20.0)

Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>

Set reporter._show_progress_info = False (#50)

This works around https://github.com/browsertron/pytest-parallel/issues/46.

It also seems to be good in general, since this also mangles the output
(and appears to be off (far behind in percentage) for when it appears etc).
